The paper discusses geocasting protocols for wireless ad hoc and sensor networks, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also presents novel protocols that utilize geographic routing mechanisms and flooding, which are common techniques in distributed systems (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between delivery rate and overhead, which is a common concern in systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NI, cs.DS, and cs.DC, followed by cs.SY and cs.IT.
